# Implementation Plan: Julia-Style LP Relaxation Lower Bound

## Decisions & Constraints

| Decision | Choice |
|----------|--------|
| Operator scope | Bilinear (`x*y`) and quadratic (`x²`) only — Phase 1 |
| LB strategy | `LB_final = max(existing_LB, LP_relax_LB)` via explicit `CompositeLowerBounder` |
| LP solver | Hard-coded Gurobi |
| EF isolation | Separate LP-relaxation context — does NOT touch the live EF |
| API design | `CompositeLowerBounder` owns orchestration; `LPRelaxationBounder` has its own `solve()` |
| Scenario-wise payload | LP relaxation **never** overwrites `lb_problem.subproblem_solutions` |
| Rebuild strategy | Preprocess once; rebuild LP per node from cached metadata |
| OA / αBB scope | Only applied to supported bilinear/quadratic structures |
| Reduced-cost BT | Phase 2 (deferred) |
| Strong branching | Phase 2 (deferred) |

---

## Julia-to-Python Mechanism Mapping

| Julia Mechanism | Julia Location | Python Equivalent | Match Level |
|----------------|----------------|-------------------|-------------|
| `preprocessSto!(P)` / `preprocessex!(Pex)` | `preprocess.jl`, `preprocessex.jl` | `EFRelaxationContext._preprocess_ef()` | Conceptual — Pyomo `generate_standard_repn(quadratic=True)` replaces Julia's MathProgBase AST traversal. **Only bilinear/quadratic `repn.quadratic_vars` are recognized; all other NL forms are detected and rejected.** |
| `relax(Pex, prex, UB)` — build LP model R with McCormick | `relax.jl:1-336` | `EFRelaxationContext._build_lp_relaxation()` | Close match — same constraints, Pyomo model API |
| `m.ext[:qbcId]` — bilinear term registry | `relax.jl:46,330` | `PreprocessResult.bilinear_registry` dict | Close match |
| `updaterelax(Rold, Pex, prex, UB)` — update LP for node | `updaterelax.jl:1-258` | `_rebuild_lp_for_node()` — rebuild LP from cached metadata | Conceptual — Python rebuilds from metadata instead of in-place coefficient mutation |
| `getRelaxLowerBound(...)` — solve LP + OA loop | `bb.jl:707-806` | `_solve_lp_with_cuts()` | Close match |
| `addOuterApproximation!(R, prex)` — OA tangent cuts | `updaterelax.jl:370-561` | `_add_oa_cuts()` — **only for `x²` and supported convex/concave quadratic groups** | Close match — scoped to supported structures only |
| `addaBB!(R, prex)` — αBB perturbation cuts | `updaterelax.jl:288-346` | `_add_abb_cuts()` — **only for indefinite quadratic blocks from preprocessing** | Close match — scoped to supported structures only |
| `@constraint(m, m.obj.aff <= U)` — UB cap | `relax.jl:42` | Explicit constraint: `obj_expr ≤ UB` | Close match |
| Combine LP+WS LBs | `bb.jl:490` | `CompositeLowerBounder.solve()` takes max | Close match |
| `R.redCosts` — reduced-cost BT | `boundT.jl:1565-1608` | Phase 2 | Deferred |

---

## Architecture Overview

```mermaid
flowchart TB
    subgraph Init["Initialization (once)"]
        A1["Subproblems built"] --> A2["EFRelaxationContext created<br>(private EF clone)"]
        A2 --> A3["_preprocess_ef():<br>Walk EF constraints via<br>generate_standard_repn(quadratic=True)<br>─ identify bilinear/x² terms<br>─ REJECT unsupported NL forms<br>─ classify convexity<br>─ compute αBB α values"]
        A3 --> A4["Store PreprocessResult<br>(cached metadata)"]
    end

    subgraph NodeLoop["Per-Node (main B&B loop)"]
        B1["CompositeLowerBounder.solve()"]
        
        B1 --> B2["Step 1: Existing LB<br>DropNonants .solve()<br>→ sets lb_problem.objective<br>→ sets lb_problem.subproblem_solutions<br>(per-scenario payload PRESERVED)"]
        
        B2 --> B3["Step 2: LP Relaxation LB<br>LPRelaxationBounder.solve()<br>→ returns lp_relax_lb<br>→ stores diagnostics in<br>lb_problem.lp_relax_diagnostics<br>(NEVER touches subproblem_solutions)"]
        
        B3 --> B4["Step 3: Combine<br>final_lb = max(existing_lb, lp_relax_lb)<br>Update lb_problem.objective ONLY<br>if lp_relax_lb > existing_lb"]
    end

    Init --> NodeLoop
```

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Payload preservation guarantee**: The `CompositeLowerBounder` updates `lb_problem.objective` to `final_lb` but **never** writes to `lb_problem.subproblem_solutions`. The existing per-scenario solutions (objectives, lifted variable values per subproblem) set by `DropNonants` remain fully intact for downstream use by branching (`tree.py:337,351,423,444,495,507`), candidate generation (`compute.py:85,88,176,179,190,272,275`), and solution inheritance (`lower_bounders.py:101-102`).

