### [MODIFY] `snoglode/components/node.py`

Add `lp_relax_diagnostics` field to `LowerBoundNodeMetrics`:

```python
class LowerBoundNodeMetrics():
    def __init__(self) -> None:
        self.feasible = None
        self.objective = None
        self.subproblem_solutions = None
        self.lp_relax_diagnostics = None   # ← NEW: dict or None
```

**What `lp_relax_diagnostics` contains** (set by `CompositeLowerBounder`):

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `existing_lb` | `float` | LB from existing DropNonants/WS pathway |
| `lp_relax_lb` | `float` | LB from LP relaxation (after all OA/αBB rounds) |
| `final_lb` | `float` | `max(existing_lb, lp_relax_lb)` |
| `lb_source` | `str` | `"existing"` or `"lp_relax"` — which one was stronger |
| `lp_relax_feasible` | `bool` | Whether the LP relaxation was feasible |
| `n_oa_rounds` | `int` | Number of OA/αBB re-solve iterations executed |
| `n_oa_cuts` | `int` | Total OA cuts added across all rounds |
| `n_abb_cuts` | `int` | Total αBB cuts added across all rounds |
| `lp_status` | `str` | Gurobi termination status string |

This field is `None` when LP relaxation is disabled. It is **read-only** from the perspective of branching/candidate-generation code — those subsystems continue to read `lb_problem.subproblem_solutions` as before.

