## Phase 1 Verification Plan

### Unit Tests
1. Build a 2-variable bilinear Pyomo model; verify `_preprocess_ef()` extracts correct BilinearEntry
2. Add a constraint with `sin(x)` → verify it is detected as unsupported and skipped with warning
3. Build LP relaxation; verify McCormick constraints have correct coefficients at given bounds
4. Solve LP → verify LB ≤ true optimal
5. Confirm `lb_problem.subproblem_solutions` is NEVER modified by CompositeLowerBounder

### Integration Test
- Run PID example with `params.enable_lp_relaxation()`
- Log comparison: `existing_lb` vs `lp_relax_lb` vs `final_lb` at each node
- Verify `final_lb ≤ true_optimal` at every node
- Verify branching/candidate-generation still work (they read `subproblem_solutions`)
- Verify convergence (gap closes)

### Cross-Validation
- Run Julia SNGO on same PID instance
- Compare root-node LP relaxation LB values
- Compare total node counts

