# Phase 2: Reduced-Cost BT & Further Enhancements (Deferred)

> [!IMPORTANT]
> Phase 2 is planned but should NOT be implemented until Phase 1 is stable and validated.

## Phase 2A: Reduced-Cost Bound Tightening

**Julia reference**: `boundT.jl:1565-1608`, called at `bb.jl:662`

#### New file: `snoglode/relaxation/reduced_cost_bt.py` (~50 lines)

After LP relaxation solve:
1. Read Gurobi reduced costs (`gurobi_persistent` solver or gurobipy model)
2. For each variable with |μ| ≥ 1e-4: tighten bound using `(UB - LB) / |μ|`
3. Propagate tightened first-stage bounds back into `node.state` and subproblem models

## Phase 2B: Possible Further Enhancements

| Enhancement | Julia Status | Priority |
|-------------|-------------|----------|
| Reduced-cost BT | Active (`boundT.jl:1565`) | **High** |
| Probing (fix var → solve LP) | Active (`bb.jl:268-401`) | Medium |
